/-
# Phase 6: assembling `MImBound` — the 2-D-orbit dispatch

(The human-facing capstones live in `Gross/Distance.lean`.)
`floor_kcombo` dispatches an arbitrary `ker ∂₂` class `kcombo c` over its 64 free-cell values:
the zero class is vacuous (`seamC 0 = 0`, so the coset is a boundary, contradicting the
hypothesis), and each of the 63 nonzero classes is a `(j,k)`-translate of one of the **5**
full-translation-orbit representatives (`MImFloorY0, Y1, Y4, Y11, Y12`), whose floor transports
via `floor_transfer` (`MImTransport §17`).  Pure `y`-shifts use a zero defect; the general
`x`-shift carries an explicit boundary defect `mkZeta …` (the §9.3 cut-shift, absorbed into the
re-indexed free chain).  `mimBound_holds` then reduces any `ζ ∈ ker ∂₂` to `kcombo` form
(`kerBasis_spans`) and applies the dispatch — discharging the last assumed `Prop` of the Gross
`[[144,12,12]]` distance proof.  The per-class shifts + boundary defects are generated by
`experiments/bb_lab/scripts/gen_assembly_2d.py` (the 2-D variant of `gen_assembly.py`).
-/
